<!-- THESIS -->
<section class="slide reveal">
  <div class="slide-label">Section 02 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Investment Thesis</div>
  <h2 class="slide-h">The problem with construction marketing<br><strong>is that it doesn't exist.</strong></h2>
  <p class="slide-sub">The .4T U.S. construction industry runs almost entirely on referrals and legacy relationships. No media company has ever owned both the narrative and the nail gun — until now.</p>
  <div class="thesis-box">
    <p class="thesis-text">FBCorp is not a media company that talks about construction. It is a <strong>media engine that sells construction</strong> — every article, episode, and broadcast drives a qualified client into one of its operating companies. The audience is the pipeline. The content is the funnel. The buildings are the exit.</p>
  </div>
